<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:08PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Montcalm County through 415 PM EDT...
At 308 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stanton, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Stanton...             Edmore...              Lakeview...
Sidney...              McBride...             Langston...
Westville...           Cedar Lake...          Entrican...
Six Lakes...           Vestaburg...           Turk Lake...
Wyman...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
